	Posts: 76-->
</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#404070" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ><img src="images/icons/icon1.gif" border="0" alt=""> <b>/hitsmode guide - Post your /hitsmode setups</b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >We had a decent thread going at the old site that included a couple of folks posting their /hitsmode configurations.  I thought we might start something up here for people who haven’t taken the time to learn it or are looking for ideas on how to set up their boxes.<br />
<br />
I have been searching for good /hitsmode information lately and found a nice guide at steelwarrior.org.  I printed it off and sat down at The Outpost and figured out what’s what.  I was pretty happy with the results.<br />
<br />
First off, here’s the guide.  It was posted by <b>Kaladornus</b>, so hats off. <br />
<br />
For whatever reason, the board here wouldn’t show it as it was posted over there, so I’ve had to touch it up a bit. It was the < > I am certain. <br />
<br />
<blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >quote:</font><hr><br />
/hitsmode  consists of 9 values. <font size="3"><b>me|my|other,  m2 - m5,  X, Y,  lines,  font,  head,  bg and width</b></font> <br />
<br />
<br />
<b>me/my/other</b> = you hitting something, you getting hit, and others' hits.<br />
<br />
-This gives 3 "temporary" boxes where battle spam shows up instead of in the <br />
chat window. If you don’t want one of the boxes, simply leave out the me, my or other line. <br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>m2/m3/m4/m5</b> = level of detail given in the new hits boxes.<br />
<br />
- m2 = Highest level of detail. "You punch a large bat for 2 points of <br />
damage."<br />
<br />
- m3 = Second highest level of detail. "Punch a large bat for 2"<br />
<br />
- m4 = You get the following text for a 2 point of damage punch, "2". Just <br />
the number.<br />
<br />
- m5 = This can ONLY be used in reporting YOUR attacks. "Punch 2".<br />
<br />
It works the same way for me, my, and other:<br />
<br />
"You punch a large bat for 2 points of damage."<br />
"Punch a large bat for 2"<br />
"2"<br />
"Punch 2"<br />
<br />
"A large rat bites YOU for 1 point of damage"<br />
"A large rat bites for 1"<br />
"1"<br />
<br />
"Guard Droolas slashes an orc centurion for 124 points of damage"<br />
"Guard Droolas slashes an orc centurion for 124"<br />
"124"<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>X and Y</b><br />
<br />
Remember coordinates from math class? Well think way back. X=0 and Y=0 <br />
[origin = (0,0)] is the top left hand corner of your screen. Add to x and <br />
the text box moves to the right. Add to y and the text box moves down.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>lines</b><br />
<br />
This is a value between 1 and 10. How many lines of text do you want to <br />
appear in the new hits box? choose wisely <br />
<br />
<br />
<b>font</b><br />
<br />
Font size. Yay! 0 to 3 I think...3 being the biggest...I THINK!<br />
<br />
<b>head</b><br />
<br />
Displays a heading on the top of the hit box indicating which it is: you <br />
hitting, getting hit, or others' hits. 0 and 1 turn it on or off.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>bg</b><br />
<br />
Toggles transparent polygons. Either the box will have no background or a <br />
tinted background. 0 and 1 turn it on or off.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>width</b><br />
<br />
The width of the box. I dont think this affects anything other than the <br />
width of the shaded area. It doesn't make text skip down to the next line or <br />
anything.<hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
Since this guide was written, Verant has added the ability to make the new windows persistent rather than them fading away when you aren't in combat.  Because I don't know what Verant calls it, I'm calling it... tada!  Persistance. You can toggle it by placing a 1 at the very end of each line.  Adding the 1 makes the windows persistent.  Leaving it empty will allow them to fade. </font></p>
	
	<p><p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >__________________<br>
<b> Bludge </b><br />
Ogre Shadowknight<br />
Fennin Ro</font></p></p>
