	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Anywhere I have "m3" simply replace it with "m2".<br />
<br />
Here is what I have (m3) compared with what you will have with "full detail" (m2)<br />
<br />
<b>For me being hit</b><br />
<br />
m3 = "An orc pawn slashes for 4"<br />
m2 = "An orc pawn slashes you for 4 points of damage"<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>For me hitting </b><br />
<br />
m3 = "Slash an orc pawn for 92"<br />
m2 = "You slash an orc pawn for 92 points of damage"<br />
<br />
<b>For someone else hitting</b><br />
<br />
m3 = "Guard Merkin slashes an orc pawn for 120"<br />
m2 = "Guard Merkin slashes an orc pawn for 120 points of damage"<br />
<br />
<br />
I wish I could post a screen cause it looks really sweet, but basically I have my chat bar centered at the bottom of the screen.<br />
<br />
Resting flush with the top of the chat bar are 3 boxes.  From left to right they are <br />
<br />
Me attacking ------ Me being attacked ------ Others attacking.<br />
<br />
I really don't see the need for the full level of detail. As you can see above, all you are losing are the words <br />
<br />
"points of damage"<br />
and<br />
"you"<br />
<br />
None of those are relevant imho and just make for longer lines of text. <br />
<br />
My set up most certainly shows others attacks.  Lots of folks turn off others attacks, but I find that I usually need to know right away when a caster is being attacked so I can go peel the critter off of em. <br />
<br />
Keep in mind, my setup will only work if you are in 1080 res</font></p>
	
