<table bgcolor="#000000" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor="#000000"  width="100%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#303070" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post900"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Bludge</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Member</font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Registered: Mar 2002<br>
<!--	Location: <br>
	Posts: 76-->
</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#303070" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ><img src="images/icons/icon1.gif" border="0" alt=""> <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >I play in the same resolution as you Mudoogul and I can't see going back.  <br />
<br />
My setup is similar to Zhomps.  My chat box is "flatter" than his becuase I figured if I was removing the hits, I didn't need it to be as large.  Instead of being stacked vertically, I have the hit boxes laid out horizontally on top of the chat boxe, with the bottom edges meeting flush with the top of the chat bar and the top edges of the boxes being the exact same height as the hotkey and spell gem boxes.<br />
<br />
Where hit hitboxes are on Zhomp's, I placed my buff box and in between the buff box and the chat window, I put my target, self and group boxes. <br />
<br />
My setup is is the exact same height as his, I just have a slightly smaller chat (7 lines shorter) window so I can keep everything on the lower 1/3 of the screen<br />
<br />
In any case, it's easy to change if you hate it. Just make a copy of your ini file on your desktop, change the 1024 and <font color="red">hitsmode</font> sections in your everquest folders .ini to use what I posted before and voila.  If you don't like it you can swap it back.<br />
<br />
Or you could simply type in the 3 <font color="red">hitsmode</font> lines above and build your other windows around it.  Just put the chat box below it.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >__________________<br>
<b> Bludge </b><br />
Ogre Shadowknight<br />
Fennin Ro</font></p></p>
